'''''Roller Coaster''''' is a [[platform game]] which contains some [[strategy]] and [[puzzle]] elements. It holds the claim of being the first [[video game]] to simulate [[amusement ride]]s.{{fact|date=June 2018}} ''Roller Coaster'' was released in [[1985 in video gaming|1985]] by [[United Kingdom|British]] video game developer [[Elite Systems]], to overwhelmingly positive reviews. It was, for a time, one of the most popular games for the [[ZX Spectrum]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.crashonline.org.uk/57/great.htm | publisher=Newsfield | work=CRASH | title=All Time Greats | access-date=2008-07-01}}</ref>{{Not in citation|date=March 2019}} A version for the Commodore 64 was planned but never released.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.gamesthatwerent.com/gtw64/roller-coaster/ | title = Roller Coaster (C64) - 1985 Elite - GTW64 | year=1985}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The game takes place in and around an [[amusement park]] after closing-time. The player takes control of the park's owner, Colonel G. Bogey. A disgruntled employee has scattered the takings all over the fairground in the form of [[money bag]]s. The goal is to collect the money.<ref name="crash24">{{cite journal|url=http://www.crashonline.org.uk/24/roller_coaster.htm|title=Roller Coaster |journal=CRASH |issue=25 |page=32 |date=1985 |access-date=2008-07-02}}</ref>

[[Image:rollercoasterscreen.gif|thumb|Start of the game]]

In order to complete the game, the player must collect every money bag which is strewn around the city-sized amusement park; even the money bags Are placed on precarious perches and in the middle of rides. In order to do this, gambles and risks will have to be taken. The player can also be killed instantaneously by some dangers. This can be caused by numerous careless acts such as jumping from a great height, getting [[skewered]] by an erratic [[turnstile]]. The player has ten lives. Once the protagonist has died ten times, the player loses and the game is over.

